article.headline: High Point 87, Anderson, S.C. 48
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored a career-best 37 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as High Point defeated Anderson 87-48 on Friday night. Reid made 16 of 20 baskets for the Panthers (5-4) en route to his third consecutive double-double. Mike Jefferson got his second consecutive double-double, scoring 10 points and getting 15 assists. Eugene Harris scored 16 points, including four 3-pointers. Brandon Young led Anderson (3-6) with 15 points. The Panthers led by 45 points at 87-42 before clearing the bench in the closing minutes. The Trojans scored the last six points of the game for the final score.
